name: Venezuelan lowland rabbit
description: The Venezuelan lowland rabbit, also known as the Barinas wild rabbit, is a species of cottontail rabbit found in western Venezuela. The largest of the rabbits within its limited distribution, it has buff- and reddish-colored fur and eats plants, mainly from the genera Sida and Malvastrum. It is closely related to the common tapeti, a smaller and more widely distributed cottontail rabbit.
